Package de.fu.junction.annotation.meta Description

Annotations which may be used to associate meta-information with code. These Java-Annotations may be used instead of Javadoc-Tags to associate information about author, version or title with Java-classes. They are not meant as a replacement for Javadoc since they are not intended to document code the way Javadoc-tags do. They are intended to be read by a program introspects it own structure (e.g. a plugin-system which offers information about where a loaded module comes from in a generic way).
